    p 
        + This example creates an authentication system that uses a
        b 
            + signed and encrypted cookie to store session data
        + . It relies on
        a 
            href https://github.com/vvo/iron-session
            title 
            code iron-session
        + .
    br 
    p 
        + It uses current best practices for authentication in the Next.js ecosystem and replicates parts of how the Vercel dashboard is built.
    br 
    p 
        b 
            + Features of the example:
    br 
    ul 
        li 
            a 
                href https://nextjs.org/docs/api-routes/dynamic-api-routes
                title 
                + API Routes
            + and
            a 
                href https://nextjs.org/docs/basic-features/data-fetching/get-server-side-props
                title 
                + getServerSideProps
            + examples.
        li 
            + The logged in status is synchronized between browser windows/tabs using
            b 
                code useUser
            + hook and the
            a 
                href https://swr.vercel.app/
                title 
                code swr
            + .
        li 
            + The layout is based on the user&#39;s logged-in/out status.
        li 
            + The session data is signed and encrypted in a cookie (this is done automatically by
            code iron-session
            + ).
    br 
    p 
        a 
            href https://github.com/vvo/iron-session
            title 
            code iron-session
        + also provides:
    br 
    ul 
        li 
            + An Express middleware, which can be used in any Node.js HTTP framework.
        li 
            + Multiple encryption keys (passwords) to allow for seamless updates or just password rotation.
        li 
            + Full TypeScript support, including session data.
